The Wedding (c. 1950) by Saul Steinberg (1914 - 1999) depicts a whimsical cartoon of a wedding scene with the bride and groom featured at the center surrounded by family members, and children posed in the foreground. The characters are screen printed in black and multicolor on a light blue silk, plain weave ground.
&amp;nbsp;
This particular textile was manufactured Piazza Prints, an independent screen printer that opened in New York in 1946, which produced many of Steinberg’s designs as wallcoverings, textiles and scarves.
